"'''One of a Kind'''" is a short story written by [[Paul Danner]] that was originally published in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 5|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 5]] by [[West End Games]] in [[February]] [[1995]]. It was made available online at [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]] on [[December 17]], [[2004]].

==Plot summary==
[[Sienn Sconn]], a down-on-his-luck charmer of a [[Thief/Legends|thief]], is passing time in the [[Binary Bar]] pondering a way to get the [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]] he owes his [[Unidentified Devaronian landlord|landlord]] for rent. [[Shandria L'hnnar]] enters the bar and sits at a table after getting a [[Alcohol/Legends|drink]] from the [[Unidentified Venaarian bar keeper|bartender]]. When [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]] arrive to arrest the rebels and L'hnnar is pursued by them, Sconn dares to rescue the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] [[Agent/Legends|agent]] and assists in her escape. L'hnnar carries stolen [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] data that could save the lives of millions if delivered to the New Republic. Sconn fights off the Imperial forces and the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Pentix Graphyt]], helping her stay a step ahead of the Imperials in a high-speed [[Speeder/Legends|speeder chase]], escorting L'hnnar to the [[Spaceport/Legends|spaceport]], where she gets to her [[BTL-S3 Y-wing starfighter/Legends|Y-Wing fighter]] and escapes off-planet. Ultimately, Sienn Sconn refuses an invitation to join the New Republic. 

